SUMMARY:Raritan Bay Waterfront Park
DESCRIPTION:Early spring birding for loons\, grebes\, gulls\, & migrants. If winds are right\, we could have a modest hawk flight. Raritan Bay Waterfront Park has long been known as a concentration point for Bonaparte’s Gulls in spring. If we’re lucky a Little Gull or Black-headed Gull could be among them. The bay usually hosts a variety of waterbirds in early spring and some landbird migrants could be around. Once you enter the park\, go north and park at the end of the lot close to the bay. Be prepared for easy walking for 3 hours. Restrooms on site. Led by Scott Barnes and Hank Burk. \nPRE-REGISTRATION REQUIRED \nCOST: $25 Members\, $30 Non-members \nCANCELLATION: NJA/CMBO programs require a minimum number of registrants to run\, five days in advance of the start of the tour but are seldom cancelled. If we do cancel\, due to lack of participation\, severe weather\, or unforeseen circumstances\, we notify all participants in advance\, and all are eligible for a full credit or refund. Participants may cancel without penalty if greater than 30 days in advance. Cancellations 10 to 30 days in advance may be subject to a 25% service charge. No refunds or credits for cancellations less than ten days in advance unless due to health emergencies. \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://njaudubon.org/event/raritan-bay-waterfront-park-10/
LOCATION:Raritan Bay Waterfront Park\, 201 John T O'Leary Boulevard\, South Amboy\, NJ\, 08879\, United States
CATEGORIES:All Things Birds,Bird Walk,Birding
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://njaudubon.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Raritan-Bay-Waterfront-Park.jpg
GEO:40.4795087379;-74.270047702
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Raritan Bay Waterfront Park 201 John T O'Leary Boulevard South Amboy NJ 08879 United States;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=201 John T O'Leary Boulevard:geo:-74.270047702,40.4795087379
END:VEVENT
